data.title: And the complete list of the area codes used in the United States
data.meta_description: List of Zip Codes - Area codes - Postal codes in Oregon, with citie, state and county serving Oregon, USA, larger cities and their corresponding codes and US territories.
data.text:
On July 1, 1963, the United States Post Office introduced the Zone Improvement Plan, or ZIP Code.ZIP codes are five-digit numbers that designate an area for the United States Postal Service.

ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan.

A ZIP Code is a 5-digit code that identifies a specific geographic delivery area.

ZIP Codes can represent an area within a state, an area that crosses state boundaries, or a single building or company that has a very high mail volume.

See all Zip Codes by State and principal US territories
